6	//! Typed cooperative-groups handles.
7	//!
8	//! This module wraps the existing low-level intrinsics (`thread::*`,
9	//! `warp::*`, `cluster::*`, `grid::*`) in typed handles so the
10	//! participating-lane mask becomes part of the type rather than a silent
11	//! integer the caller has to remember.
12	//!
13	//! Each emitted PTX collective instruction (`vote.sync`, `shfl.sync`,
14	//! `match.sync`, ...) is byte-identical to the equivalent raw
15	//! `warp::*_sync` call — the participation mask folds at compile time.
16	//! Whether the wrapper *function* itself folds away is a separate
17	//! question, decided by rustc's MIR `Inline` cost threshold: for the
18	//! smallest wrappers it does and the call site is indistinguishable
19	//! from the raw form, but for larger wrappers the wrapper survives as
20	//! a `.visible .func` and the call site emits a `call.uni`. The
21	//! `hashmap_v2` example ships `find_kernel_warp` (raw) and
22	//! `find_kernel_warp_typed` (this API) side by side as an in-tree
23	//! reference for the current cost of that trade-off.
24	//!
25	//! # The universal trio
26	//!
27	//! Every group type implements [`ThreadGroup`] and exposes the same
28	//! three operations:
29	//!
30	//! - [`size`](ThreadGroup::size)         — how many threads are in this group
31	//! - [`thread_rank`](ThreadGroup::thread_rank) — my index within this group, `0..size`
32	//! - [`sync`](ThreadGroup::sync)         — barrier scoped to this group
33	//!
34	//! # The hierarchy
35	//!
36	//! ```text
37	//! Grid             this_grid()                grid::sync()             cooperative launch only
38	//! Cluster          this_cluster()             cluster::cluster_sync()  sm_90+
39	//! ThreadBlock      this_thread_block()        thread::sync_threads()
40	//!   WarpTile<32>     block.tiled_partition()  ballot/shfl/match        full warp
41	//!   WarpTile<N<32>>  block.tiled_partition()  warp::sync_mask          sub-warp tile
42	//!   CoalescedThreads coalesced_threads()      warp::sync_mask          runtime active mask
43	//! ```
44	//!
45	//! # Reductions and scans
46	//!
47	//! On top of the typed handles this module also ships the four
48	//! collective primitives `warp_reduce`, `warp_scan`, `block_reduce`,
49	//! and `block_scan`, generic over a [`ReduceOp`](ops::ReduceOp) trait
50	//! with concrete impls for `Sum`/`Min`/`Max` (`u32`/`i32`/`f32`) and
51	//! `BitAnd`/`BitOr`/`BitXor` (`u32` only). Block-scoped variants
52	//! take a `*mut SharedArray<T, NUM_WARPS>` for scratch and obey the
53	//! standard "block-sync between back-to-back uses of the same scratch"
54	//! contract documented on each function.
55	//!
56	//! # Example: warp-wide ballot from `find_kernel_warp`
57	//!
58	//! ```rust,ignore
59	//! use cuda_device::cooperative_groups::{this_thread_block, ThreadGroup, WarpCollective};
60	//!
61	//! let block = this_thread_block();
62	//! let warp = block.tiled_partition::<32>();
63	//!
64	//! let m_h2 = warp.ballot(tag == h2);
65	//! if m_h2 != 0 {
66	//!     let leader = m_h2.trailing_zeros();
67	//!     let payload = warp.shfl(my_payload, leader);
68	//!     // ...
69	//! }
70	//! ```
71	//!
72	//! Switching to a 16-lane sub-warp tile is one line:
73	//!
74	//! ```rust,ignore
75	//! let tile = block.tiled_partition::<16>();
76	//! let m_h2 = tile.ballot(tag == h2);  // mask is 0xFFFF or 0xFFFF0000
77	//! ```
78	
79	use crate::{cluster, grid, shared::SharedArray, thread, warp};
